Contributing to OSS as Compensation
========================

* Speaker   : William Berry
* Available : Whenever 
* Length    : 20-30min

Description
-----------

While the benefits of OSS participation for the enterprise are plentyful, the direct benfit to employees is an often overlooked consideration.  In this session we'll investigate some of the many ways a well defined OSS contribution program can improve employee engagement and performance. 

---------------
[*All things below are optional*]

Speaker Bio
-----------

In a previous life Bill crafted scenery for Broadway, a la Pirates of Penzance, but now crafts software for the enterprise, a la Pirates of Silicon Valley.  In his roles as Technical Lead and Application Architect for The Retail Equation, Bill has lead service integrations with Fortune 500 retailers, curated DevOps initiatives and always enjoys building high performance, multi-tenant distributed data APIs.  As a deeply curious engineer, he enjoys pairing complex problems with simple and elegant solutions. Striving for meaningful change, Bill believes that cultural and technical progress is best made through evolution and not revolution. 

